Learner's Maya Glyph Guide

​Concordance Table
John Pedersen, August 2025

This Concordance covers all known Classic Maya logograms and syllabograms inasmuch as the systems given here cover them (new glyphs continue to be added over time). This includes the logograms and syllabograms on the Home page. It provides a cross-reference for the three main glyph-classification systems: (i) the well-established "Thompson numbers" (T#'s), often encountered in published papers; (ii) Bonn's codes, the recent rework and extension of the Thompson numbers by the Bonn University TWKM Project; and (iii) the MHD codes, used in the Maya Hieroglyphic Database. Corresponding CMGG entries, which provide many further glyph-variant examples as well as linguistic and other notes, are also given when they exist.

Note: Columns with an arrow in their heading can be sorted: just click on the heading (to regain original T# order, reload the page). For example, sorting on the last ("CMGG Entry") column brings glyphs for the same word together and sorting on the "MHD Translation" column gives all syllabograms first (see also the Logograms and Syllabograms grids available on the Home page). Sorting on the MHD Images/Codes column will group rows according to the MHD Classification System. For sources see here. For further explanation of the table information and its use, please see Concordance Help.
Warning: The MHD Catalog has undergone significant changes in 2024-2025 with respect to readings and T-numbers, not all of which are reflected below. For critical work, please use the MHD Catalog. In addition, Bonn released a major update to their system on 2025-08-01; this has not yet been incorporated here.

Please send any questions, suggestions for improvement and any other comments to maya.glyphs@yahoo.com.
